Foraminifers are visible (medium sand-size). Burrows are observed.
Burrows are observed. Bioturbated contact at ~40 cm. Pyrite fills burrows (14-52 cm, 65 cm). Foraminifers are visible (medium sand-size). Big forams at ~113 cm interval.
Interbedded layers of slightly different color (reddish and grayish) with slightly bioturbated contacts. More forams are visible in 82-84 cm.

Generally uniform with some color alternation in burrows. Slight bioturbation throughout. Few foraminifers in clay at 23 cm level. Pyritized burrow at 132 cm.

Burrows throughout. Color alternation visible in burrows, and some color change along core, but all pretty much the same. At 69 cm, gradational, bioturbated contact between slightly reddish above to grayer below (maybe part of bedding in interval). Forams are visible (medium sand-size) throughout.
